The "BOSS" name and the all-caps brand spelling are used as the
canonical project identifier; the lowercase `boss-` prefix appears
on crate paths, binary names, env vars, and systemd units where
uppercase would break tooling.

The acronym expands to "Beer Open Source Software — for System
Modeling," named in tribute to Stafford Beer (1926-2002), the
British cybernetician whose Viable System Model + Cyberstride /
Project Cybersyn work is the intellectual lineage this project
sits in. Algedonic, LLC has no affiliation with the Stafford Beer
estate; the project name is a tribute, not an endorsement.
